value.title: Ilhan Omar mobilizing progressives to push Biden further left
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., said in an interview that Democrats will have "a cohort of progressives" who will try to influence 2020 presidential nominee Joe Biden should he be elected.

value.title: Biden again clarifies oil 'transition' comment, says industry 'not going to go away'
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden on Monday clarified his oil industry "transition" comment in two separate interviews with TV stations in Pittsburgh and Dallas.

value.title: Biden raises idea of rotating Supreme Court justices: 'There is some literature among constitutional scholars'
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden indicated on Monday that he might be open to shifting Supreme Court justices to lower courts if elected president, noting that he hadn't made any "judgement" yet on the issue.

value.title: Civil rights attorney Leo Terrell: Biden has done nothing for Black community 'other than insulting' them
value.excerpt: Civil rights attorney Leo Terrell rips 2020 Democratic nominee Joe Biden for his failure to address issues impacting the Black community during his 36-year career in the United States Senate on his new Fox Nation show "Larry & Leo 2.

value.title: Pence campaigns with 'medically informed' approach to events after staffers test positive for COVID-19
value.excerpt: Vice President Pence has returned to the campaign trail after key staffers tested positive for the novel coronavirus, however his team is taking a “thoughtful” and “medically-informed” approach to his travel this week in the final stretch until Election Day.

value.title: Kamala Harris thinks she can laugh her way through serious questions: Pavlich
value.excerpt: Editor Katie Pavlich called Democratic vice-presidential nominee Sen. Kamala Harris “the most far-left Democrat in Washington, D.C.," and said Joe Biden picked her to "make sure that the left wing of the party felt comfortable" that they would have a voice in his administration.

value.title: Jared Kushner: Peace deals 'are much harder than President Trump is making them look'
value.excerpt: Peace deals “are much harder than President Trump is making them look,” White House adviser Jared Kushner, who has been involved in brokering the Middle East peace deals, told “Fox & Friends” on Monday.

value.title: Pence tests negative for coronavirus again as Democrats push him to skip Barrett vote
value.excerpt: Senate Democrats are telling Vice President Mike Pence to stay away from Judge Amy Coney Barrett's confirmation vote on Capitol Hill after five people in Pence's orbit tested positive for coronavirus last week, although the vice president tested negative again on Monday.

value.title: ’60 Minutes’ airs Trump interview cut short by president
value.excerpt: “60 Minutes” aired the interview on Sunday night. Stahl warned viewers that the interview started politely but “ended, regrettably, contentiously.”

value.title: Pence says Biden, Harris should stop playing politics with COVID-19 vaccine
FBI Director Christopher Wray will be removed from post if Trump is re-elected, source tells Fox News
value.excerpt: Reports are surfacing that President Trump will fire FBI Director Christopher Wray should he win reelection next Tuesday.

value.title: NYPD cop suspended for using loudspeaker to say 'Trump 2020' while on duty
value.excerpt: A New York police officer has reportedly been suspended without pay for using the department vehicle’s loudspeaker to proclaim his support for President Donald Trump’s 2020 campaign.

value.title: Whitmer thanks FBI, blames Trump admin after kidnapping plot foiled
value.excerpt: Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer blamed the Trump administration for rhetoric that she claimed led to a kidnapping plot against her, after the Trump campaign accused her of encouraging attempts on the president's life.

value.title: RNC Chair McDaniel calls out Biden for energy comments: 'He's lying to the American people'
value.excerpt: Republican National Committee Chair Ronna McDaniel accused Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden of "lying to the American people" regarding his energy policies, specifically regarding fracking and the oil industry.

value.title: Biden says in video he has created 'voter fraud organization'
value.excerpt: Democratic nominee Joe Biden said his team has created "the most extensive and inclusive voter fraud organization in the history of American politics" in a recent video.

value.title: Pence defends Trump COVID-19 response, claims administration 'literally saved hundreds of thousands'
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has again defended the Trump administration's response to the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: AOC tells Jane Fonda it's OK to be Trump's 'public enemy No. 1': 'That's a good thing'
value.excerpt: Being attacked President Trump is a “badge of honor," U.S. Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez told actress Jane Fonda during an online interview last week.

value.title: Harris: Voting for president is about ‘honoring ancestors’ who fought for civil rights
value.excerpt: Democratic vice presidential candidate Kamala Harris headed to Cleveland  Saturday to reach out to voters in one of the closest races for the presidency in the U.S.

value.title: Trump told donors holding Republican Senate would be 'very tough': report
value.excerpt: President Trump privately told donors it would be “very tough” for Republicans to maintain control of the Senate come November because he cannot support all of the party’s candidates, according to a report.

value.title: Biden claims Amy Coney Barrett wants to overturn Obamacare
value.excerpt: 2020 Democratic nominee Joe Biden on Saturday said Supreme Court nominee Amy Coney Barrett wants to overturn ObamaCare.

value.title: Jennifer Aniston discourages voters from supporting Kanye West, casts her ballot for Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Jennifer Aniston officially voted in the 2020 presidential election. In addition to revealing who she voted for, she also discouraged voters from supporting Kanye West.

value.title: Andrew McCarthy: Joe and Hunter Biden should not be investigated by special counsel
value.excerpt: It is rational to suspect that there is criminality by the Bidens, but there is no good reason to appoint a special counsel to investigate them.

value.title: Trump Jr. floats 2024 run for president: ‘This will make the lib heads explode’
value.excerpt: Donald Trump Jr. posted a photo to Instagram Saturday standing in front of a “Don Jr 2024” sign, teasing that prospect. “Hahahahaha. Oh boy. This was a sign I saw up

value.title: Pence calls on Biden to 'come forward and come clean' with answers on son Hunter's scandal
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence called on his predecessor, Joe Biden, to be frank and honest with the American people Friday about whether he was involved in or benefited from his son Hunter's overseas business interests.

value.title: Democratic Rep. Xochitl Torres Small slams Biden over oil remarks at debate, says policy is 'out of touch'
value.excerpt: Biden said he would pursue policies that would “transition from the oil industry” if elected to office.

value.title: Gregg Jarrett: Hunter Biden laptop scandal — Even if Joe Biden wins, there's no way out now
value.excerpt: In the Hunter Biden laptop scandal, the unresolved and trenchant questions are: how much did Joe Biden know and to what extent was he involved

value.title: Lara Logan slams Biden for playing ‘Russia card’ in response to Hunter Biden email allegations
value.excerpt: 2020 Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden played the "Russian information warfare" card to dodge questions pertaining to his son Hunter Biden's foreign dealings, Fox Nation host Lara Logan said on Friday.

value.title: Joy Behar says Trump should be charged with ‘crimes against humanity’ over immigration policy
value.excerpt: The View” co-host Joy Behar said on Friday that President Trump and members of his administration should be charged with “crimes against humanity” because of its immigration policy and vowed to not “be a part of a country” that separates children from their parents.

value.title: Trump announces peace deal between Sudan and Israel, says more nations will normalize relations
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump announced Friday that Sudan will start to normalize ties with Israel, making it the third Arab state to do so as part of U.S.-brokered deals in the run-up to Election Day.

value.title: New Jersey judge throws out Trump campaign mail-in ballot lawsuit
value.excerpt: A federal judge in New Jersey Thursday threw out an August lawsuit filed by the Trump campaign in relation to mail-in voting.
